rComments: The second I stepped into my first class I instantly regretted it having heard his accent - it really is quite bad. Concepts were not explained so well and it seemed like I had to learn the material through using the textbook. As the semester progressed I learned how to follow lectures more effectively and it seemed he wasn't AS BAD as I thought.

one of the worst prof I met in Uoft, Try to avoid his session as much as possible. Extremely awful accent, useless class slides.
